		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Quellious Summer Lottery - Tickets Now on Sale!</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=429632" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top">
		    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
<p>
<B>Quellious Players</B></p>
<p>
As a means of adding some excitement to the Quellious server I am administering a very well organized lottery that I invite and encourage you to play.</p>
<p>
This lottery will have a guaranteed 5,000pp payoff even if ticket sales do not generate that much revenue. I am personally guaranteeing this amount and will pay with my own money if the jackpot is less than I anticipate.</p>
<p>
Let it be known that I have always underestimated my lotteries. I believe I will sell a very minimum of 5,000 tickets to this lottery, and my goal is 10,000. You do not want to miss this folks.</p>
<p>
Ticket sales started May 8th and will continue up until the drawing. I will provide the details briefly below:</p>
<p>
<B>How much do tickets cost?</B></p>
<p>
Tickets are 1pp each. Buy 5 and get 1 FREE.</p>
<p>
<B>What can I win?</B></p>
<p>
The money generated from the ticket sales will be awarded to the 1st place, 2nd place, and 3rd place winners.</p>
<ul>
<li>1st Place wins 70% net revenue
<li>2nd Place wins 20% net revenue
<li>3rd Place wins 10% net revenue
</ul>
<p>
In addition, there will be AT LEAST 10 donated loot items awarded. These loot items will all have a value of at least 100pp each. Many loot items in the past were worth over 5,000pp each. Don't think the loot will be cheap. I will not accept donated garbage.</p>
<p>
<B>How do I buy tickets?</B></p>
<p>
You can ONLY buy tickets directly through me...Morthan Anuff. I am traveling through most zones each day shouting hotkeyed lotto messages that contain all relevant lottery information. Once you hear the shouts...come to me quickly. I will not stay in a zone long.</p>
<p>
<B>How can I trust you?</B></p>
<p>
You can't. If you are the type of person that requires someone to earn your trust, then I suggest you do not play this first lottery. There will be more to come. There is nothing wrong with being skeptical. Most importantly, I do NOT have the time or energy to convince you ingame of my honesty. I do this for fun and don't need the stress.</p>
<p>
If you don't trust me...don't play. Its that simple.</p>
<p>
If you happen to decide to not play this lottery...please try to come to the drawing. There are usually at least 100 people or more gathered around at my lottery drawings. It is alot of fun and makes for some great screenshots.</p>
<p>
<B>How many lotteries have you done?</B></p>
<p>
I have done 13 major lotteries on Bertoxxolous, but this will be my first lottery on Quellious. Once this lottery is over and the winners have received their winnings promptly...people will realize I am for real and have no intention of scamming people out of their hard earned money.</p>
<p>
<B>When is the drawing?</B></p>
<p>
The drawing will be at approximately 11:00 pm eastern on Saturday, June 16th.</p>
<p>
<B>Where will the drawing be?</B></p>
<p>
The drawing will be in North Ro where most people will be able to attend without any real dangers. I believe there is some sort of temple near the water or dock that would make an ideal drawing location.</p>
<p>
I will scope out North Ro soon and decide exactly where I will do the drawing. I am even considering wacking Dorn and holding the drawing in his little camp. I hate that bastard.</p>
<p>
The first 13 lottery drawings all took place on the dock in Oasis. I don't think that zone can handle a lottery this size, so North Ro seems better.</p>
<p>
<B>Must we be present to win?</B></p>
<p>
Not at all. Many past winners were not even online at the time of the drawing. If you win your friends will have heard and the message will get to you.</p>
<p>
I always track down winners and have yet to have even a slight problem locating and paying a winner.</p>
<p>
<B>How do you do the drawing?</B></p>
<p>
Very simple folks. Here is the math in a hypothetical situation. Lets say I issue a total of 10,000 tickets:</p>
<p>
10,000 tickets issued<br>
-8,000 tickets sold<br>
---------<br>
= 2,000 tickets issued FREE (Buy 5, Get 1 FREE)</p>
<p>
So, we have 8,000pp in ticket revenue</p>
<p>
#1: 8kpp lesss my 10% cut = 7,200pp in prize money<br>
#2: First place wins 70% or 5,040pp<br>
#3: Second place wins 20% or 1,440pp<br>
#4: Third place wins 720pp</p>
<p>
The winners are determined by random draw.</p>
<p>
If 10k ticket #'s issued then in front of everybody I will do random rolls for the 3 winners. I always start with the 3rd place winner first...to build the suspense.</p>
<p>
/random 10000</p>
<p>
This draw will produce a random number between 1 and 10,000. Whoever holds that ticket number wins that prize level.</p>
<p>
I will continue this process until all money prizes and donated loot prizes have been awarded.</>
<p>
<B>Do GM's know of this lottery?</B></p>
<p>
I always petition to have a guide present at the drawings. I even invite them to do the random draws, but they have always turned me down stating they are not permitted to interfere or participate in player events. The GM being there is a comfort to the skeptics that think somehow the lottery is rigged. If it is rigged...they will know.</p>
<p>
<B>If the drawing is on june 16th why can't I wait till then to buy tickets?</B></p>
<p>
#1 I may end the Buy 5, get 1 FREE deal as ticket sales start picking up. Sales are ALWAYS slow in the beginning as people have no real incentive to play when the jackpot is low.</p>
<p>
#2 The days before the drawing I will be slammed and will NOT be able to return every /tell. Many people have expressed regret that they didn't buy tickets when they had the chance.</p>
<p>
The few hours before the drawing will be chaotic. Do NOT think you'll be able to buy tickets easily. I may simply never get to you by the time the drawing time comes. You cannot win if you don't play...so buy the tickets right away.</p>
<p>
Ok, good luck to everyone!</p>
<p>
Morthan Anuff<br>
<I>"When enough just isn't enough..."</I><br>
35th Season Wood Elf Druid<br>
<I>Greater Druids</I></p>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
