				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Everyone:<BR>
<BR>
2700 tickets issued so far. About 20% of these have been FREE or nonrevenue generating. The total in the jackpot available for payout is about 1900pp after I deduct my 10% of gross ticket revenue.<BR>
<BR>
I strongly suspect the total jackpot will far exceed 10,000pp. The usuals scenario is the actual day of the drawing the jackpot almost doubles. we will see.<BR>
<BR>
Starting soon I will be accepting donations for the lottery. These donations will be awarded in the same fashion as the money prizes.<BR>
<BR>
I will request loot donations to have a market value of 250pp or greater. Originally I thought 100pp would be the lowest priced items accepted, but I am getting tells and am now realizing too many people and guilds are willing to pitch in great loot.<BR>
<BR>
And to the person who made a comment about my retaining 10% as being a &quot;scam,&quot; well what level are you? This lottery started around May 8th and will continue until June 16th. How many levels will you make during that period of time? How mcuh money and loot will you acquire? I am on hold. During the time I am doing this lottery I make nothing at all. I gain no experience. I acquire no loot. My bank account does not grow.<BR>
<BR>
Several days ago a friend in real life quit playing EQ. He had 5 characters including a level 56 druid and a 42 level warrior. He was considered quite wealthy with items worth well over 150,000pp.<BR>
<BR>
Well, when he quit EQ he gave everything he had on all characters to me and another friend. This means I am quite wealthy for being level 35. Making 700pp to 1000pp off a lottery is far from being a scam...unless you mean &quot;I&quot; am getting scammed. I am not doing this lottery to become rich or to screw people out of money. I'm not exactly hurting for money.<BR>
<BR>
Ok, enough defensiveness...<BR>
<BR>
Good luck all!<BR>
<BR>
Morthan Anuff<BR>
35th Season Druid<BR>
Quellious<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

